  <body>
    <div class="content">
      <div class="presentation">
        <h1 class="title">
          Hi visitors, I am thrilled to introduce my brand new design system built with
          Vue 3. This project is the result of many hours of work an reflection. I am
          excited to share with you the details of its design and features.
        </h1>

        <h2 class="subtitle">Why a Design System?</h2>

        <p class="paragraph">
          For several years I've been working on user interfaces involving component
          creation such as buttons, text input etc... Different teams different approaches
          to implementing similar designs and logic... As I want to level-up on more
          topics such as frontend architecture I needed a library that would speed up the
          dev process letting me focus on how the information flows rather than how it
          looks. A design system is crucial for ensuring consistency and efficiency in the
          development of our applications. It standardizes components, styles, and best
          practices, facilitating collaboration between designers and developers.
        </p>

        <h2 class="subtitle">Why Vue?</h2>

        <p class="paragraph">
          Meanwhile I am proficient on both React and Vue I chose Vue 3 for its
          reactivity, flexibility, and active community. Vue 3 offers improved
          performance, better state management, and a more intuitive syntax, making it an
          ideal choice for building a modern and scalable design system.
        </p>

        <h2 class="subtitle">Next steps</h2>
        <ul>
          <li class="next">Storybook setup to provide components testing</li>
          <li class="next">Playwright setup to automate testing</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="spacer"></div>
        <div class="technos">
          Made with
          <Icon name="vuejs" />
          <Icon name="astrojs" />
        </div>
      </div>
